goals.question: What is the distribution of node sizes in the tree?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of node sizes in the tree and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the average size of nodes in the tree?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the central tendency and variability of node sizes in the tree.

goals.question: What is the distribution of parent node identifiers in the tree?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of parent node identifiers and identify any patterns or clusters.

goals.question: What is the most common node name in the tree?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the most frequently occurring node names in the tree and potentially identify any naming conventions or patterns.

goals.question: What is the relationship between node size and parent node identifier?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of size and parent fields
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any patterns or trends in the relationship between node size and parent node identifier.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["size"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of node sizes in the tree?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 7))
    ax.boxplot(data['size'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average size of nodes in the tree?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_ylabel('Size')
    ax.axhline(data['size'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["size"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['parent'], bins=30, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['parent'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['parent'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of parent node identifiers in the tree?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(name_counts.index, name_counts.values)
    plt.title('What is the most common node name in the tree?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['parent', 'size']]
    plt.scatter(data['parent'], data['size'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between node size and parent node identifier?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
